      • getForceLogin

        public java.lang.Boolean getForceLogin()
        Returns the value of field 'forceLogin'. The field 'forceLogin' has the following description: Prior to release 4.0 of AE Services, this parameter was not supported, because login was always forced. Beginning with release 4.0 of AE Services, this flag is supported, and login will be forced only if the application requests it to be so.

        Formerly, even if the phone was already logged in or the phone/extension was already registered by your application or another application, your request for registration would be forced. Henceforth, if this parameter is not explicitly set to true, and Commmunication Manager determines that the maximum number of registrations for an extension has been reached, then the client should expect to receive a RegistrationConstants.EXTENSION_IN_USE in the RegisterTerminalResponse.

        Defaults to false. Optional.

        Returns:
        Boolean

      • getSharedControl

        public java.lang.Boolean getSharedControl()
        Returns the value of field 'sharedControl'. The field 'sharedControl' has the following description: This field is deprecated; use dependencyMode and mediaMode instead. If you had previously been setting this field to true, then set dependencyMode to DEPENDENT and mediaMode to NONE. If you had previously been setting this field to false, or had not been setting it at all, then you can set dependencyMode to MAIN and explicitly set the desired value for mediaMode.
        Returns:
        Boolean

      • getTelecommuterExtension

        public java.lang.String getTelecommuterExtension()
        Returns the value of field 'telecommuterExtension'. The field 'telecommuterExtension' has the following description: Telecommuter media allows an application to direct the media to go to a real telephone. The real telephone can be inside or outside of the Communication Manager domain. Set this field to the to the telephone number of the real telephone to which you are directing the media. As of release 4.0 of AE Services, if you set telecommuterExtension then you must also set mediaMode to MediaMode.TELECOMMUTER and dependencyMode to DependencyMode.MAIN. Optional.
        Returns:
        String

      • getUnicodeScript

        public java.lang.Integer getUnicodeScript()
        Returns the value of field 'unicodeScript'. The field 'unicodeScript' has the following description: This allows a DMCC device to receive unicode formatted display updates and button labels. This is intended for internationalization. The Communication Manager must be administered with proper unicode scripts for this feature to work.

        Defaults to 0. Optional.

        Returns:
        Integer
